  <pbcoreTitle titleType="Other">Dry Spell</pbcoreTitle>
  <pbcoreDescription>Content: The film is the story of a man who cannot express his emotions of loss and the eventual torrent of emotion that overwhelms him because of it. Written, directed and produced by Andres Garcia-Price, Dry Spell is based on the 1950's short story Men Don't Cry by renowned Costa Rican novelist Fabian Dobles, Garcia-Price's great uncle. Garcia-Price received permission to adapt the story from his great-uncle but Dobles died before the film was complete.??Aired as part of Intensity TV 113 intense Drama: on Death and Dying"</pbcoreDescription>
